text: Brenna Bird (born as Brenda Findley in 1976) is an American Republican politician and lawyer. She has operated under the Iowa Attorney General from 2023 and onwards. ==The career== Bird did over seven years with the United States Representative Steve King beginning in January 2003 and ending May 2010. Under the 2010 election, Bird ran for the Iowa Attorney General. She, however, lost to Iowa imcumbent Tom Miller by eleven percent. Bird again ran against Miller under the 2022 Iowa Attorney General Election. She won that race. ==References== Category:Politicians from Iowa Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians Category:Living people Category:1976 births
